The proposed research aims to develop a **pragmatically-aware QA framework** that integrates formal linguistic features (e.g., projection, cancellability) into neural models via structured supervision. This approach leverages annotated clinical text and targets improved classification, validation, and response strategies for each inference type—enhancing accuracy, safety, and explainability in AI-driven health interactions.

